"title": "5289: debt",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5289",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>God is the Maker and sustainer of all things and therefore all creatures owe everything to him. Scripture provides guidance concerning both debt and debtors.</p>\n<h2>Everyone is in debt to God as Creator</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor4:7\">1CO 4:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut8:17-Deut8:18\">DEU 8:17–8:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr29:11-1Chr29:13\">1CH 29:11–29:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps24:1-Ps24:2\">PSA 24:1–24:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl5:19\">ECC 5:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:17\">ACT 14:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:25\">ACT 17:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:17\">1TI 6:17</a></p>\n<h2>Everyone is in debt to God as law-giver</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:19\">ROM 3:19</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas2:10\">JAS 2:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut27:26\">DEU 27:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps49:7-Ps49:8\">PSA 49:7–49:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal3:8-Mal3:10\">MAL 3:8–3:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:41-Luke7:42\">LUK 7:41–7:42</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:10\">GAL 3:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:3\">GAL 5:3</a></p>\n<h2>Believers are in debt to God as Redeemer</h2>\n<h3>He has paid their debt</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:13\">GAL 3:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor8:9\">2CO 8:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:18\">1PE 1:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev5:9\">REV 5:9</a></p>\n<h3>A sense of debt inspires devotion to God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps116:12\">PSA 116:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:41-Luke7:47\">LUK 7:41–7:47</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:12\">ROM 8:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:20\">1CO 6:20</a></p>\n<h3>Indebtedness to God affects attitude to others</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:8\">MAT 10:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:12\">MAT 6:12</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:4\">LUK 11:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:21-Matt18:35\">MAT 18:21–18:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:16\">1JN 3:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John4:11\">1JN 4:11</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of people in debt</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam22:2\">1SA 22:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs4:1\">2KI 4:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh5:4\">NEH 5:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:25-Matt5:26\">MAT 5:25–5:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:23-Matt18:35\">MAT 18:23–18:35</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke16:1-Luke16:8\">LUK 16:1–16:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom4:4\">ROM 4:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas5:4\">JAS 5:4</a></p>\n<h2>Debts must be paid</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:13\">LEV 19:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs4:7\">2KI 4:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps37:21\">PSA 37:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom13:7-Rom13:8\">ROM 13:7–13:8</a></p>\n<h2>Social ills result from debt</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh5:3-Neh5:5\">NEH 5:3–5:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job24:3\">JOB 24:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job24:9\">JOB 24:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps109:11\">PSA 109:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek18:12-Ezek18:13\">EZK 18:12–18:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek22:12\">EZK 22:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos2:6\">AMO 2:6</a></p>\n<h2>OT laws sought to minimise debt</h2>\n<h3>By commanding generous lending to the poor</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod22:25\">EXO 22:25</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:35-Lev25:36\">LEV 25:35–25:36</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut15:7-Deut15:11\">DEU 15:7–15:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps15:5\">PSA 15:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov19:17\">PRO 19:17</a></p>\n<h3>By curbing exploitation of debtors</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:37-Lev25:43\">LEV 25:37–25:43</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut24:6\">DEU 24:6</a></p>\n<h3>By cancelling debts every seventh year</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut15:1-Deut15:3\">DEU 15:1–15:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut31:10\">DEU 31:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh10:31\">NEH 10:31</a></p>\n<h2>Preventatives against needless debt</h2>\n<h3>Keeping short accounts</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:25\">MAT 5:25</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom13:8\">ROM 13:8</a></p>\n<h3>Remembering the evil consequences</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov22:7\">PRO 22:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:26\">MAT 5:26</a></p>\n<h2>Debts to the state</h2>\n<h3>Paying taxes</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:17-Matt22:21\">MAT 22:17–22:21</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:14-Mark12:17\">MRK 12:14–12:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:22-Luke20:25\">LUK 20:22–20:25</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom13:6-Rom13:7\">ROM 13:6–13:7</a></p>\n<h3>Civic honour</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom13:7\">ROM 13:7</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Debts to employees</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom4:4\">ROM 4:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:13\">LEV 19:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas5:4\">JAS 5:4</a></p>\n<h2>Debts within the church</h2>\n<h3>Towards Christian workers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phlm1:18-Phlm1:19\">PHM 1:18–1:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:7-1Cor9:12\">1CO 9:7–9:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:6\">GAL 6:6</a></p>\n<h3>Towards the unsaved</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:14\">ROM 1:14</a></strong></p>\n<h3>The indebtedness of the Gentile church towards the Jerusalem church</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:26-Rom15:27\">ROM 15:26–15:27</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Debts to be cancelled</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:12\">MAT 6:12</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:4\">LUK 11:4</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor13:5\">1CO 13:5</a></p>\n<h2>Debts one should never pay</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:17\">ROM 12:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:9\">1PE 3:9</a></p>\n<h2>A debt one can never cease paying</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom13:8-Rom13:10\">ROM 13:8–13:10</a></strong></p>",
